Maggie MANZO, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. NATIONAL RESERVE INSURANCE COMPANY OF ILLINOIS, Also Known as National Reserve Insurance Company, Defendant-Appellant. No. 148. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Jan. 4, 1937. Powers, Kaplan & Berger, of New York City (David A. Ticktin and Milton Adler, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Charles B. Dullea, of New York City (Alfred B. Nathan, of New York City, Joseph P. Walsh, of St. George, S. I., N. Y., and Benjamin Lewis, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
